snippet: The Commerce Department said that wholesale inventories slipped 0.1 percent in October as sluggish sales have given businesses little incentive to restock.
lead_paragraph: The Commerce Department said that wholesale inventories slipped 0.1 percent in October as sluggish sales have given businesses little incentive to restock.

headline.main: U.S. Wholesale Inventories Shrink, Hinting at More Anemic Growth
